{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01T61KBGEtCgW6svKds5yses","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# ray/deploy_cluster\n2\t# Deploy a Ray head, head Service, and worker deployment from provided manifests\n3\t\n4\tprompt: |\n5\t  A ray-client pod is running in the ray namespace, but no Ray cluster exists yet.\n6\t\n7\t  Your task: deploy a Ray head, a Ray head Service, and a Ray worker deployment\n8\t  using the manifests in:\n9\t  - cases/ray/deploy_cluster/resource/ray-head.yaml\n10\t  - cases/ray/deploy_cluster/resource/ray-head-service.yaml\n11\t  - cases/ray/deploy_cluster/resource/ray-worker.yaml\n12\t\n13\t  Requirements:\n14\t  - Keep ray-client unchanged.\n15\t  - The worker deployment should run {{params.worker_replicas}} replicas.\n16\t\n17\t  Use this command to validate:\n18\t  ```bash\n19\t  kubectl -n ray exec ray-client -- python -c \"import ray; ray.init(address='ray-head:6379'); print('ok'); ray.shutdown()\"\n20\t  ```\n21\t\n22\t  Success criteria: both deployments are ready and the command prints \"ok\".\n23\t\n24\tparams:\n25\t  worker_replicas:\n26\t    default: 2\n27\t    description: Number of replicas for the Ray worker deployment\n28\t\n29\tnamespace_contract:\n30\t  required_roles: []\n31\t\n32\tmetrics:\n33\t  - time_to_first_mutation\n34\t\n35\tpreconditionUnits:\n36\t  - name: ray_env_ready\n37\t    on_probe_fail: skip\n38\t    probe:\n39\t      - command: \"kubectl -n ray get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\"\n40\t        timeout_sec: 10\n41\t    apply:\n42\t      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'kubectl delete namespace ray --ignore-not-found=true --wait=false; kubectl wait --for=delete namespace/ray --timeout=300s 2>/dev/null || true'\"\n43\t        timeout_sec: 360\n44\t        sleep: 2\n45\t      - command: \"kubectl create namespace ray\"\n46\t        sleep: 0\n47\t      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'kubectl -n ray get pod ray-client >/dev/null 2>&1 || kubectl -n ray apply -f cases/ray/deploy_cluster/resource/ray-client.yaml'\"\n48\t        sleep: 1\n49\t      - command: \"kubectl -n ray wait --for=condition=Ready pod/ray-client --timeout=600s\"\n50\t        timeout_sec: 660\n51\t        sleep: 1\n52\t    verify:\n53\t      - command: \"kubectl -n ray get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\"\n54\t        timeout_sec: 10\n55\t\n56\toracle:\n57\t  verify:\n58\t    commands:\n59\t      - command: \"python3 cases/ray/deploy_cluster/oracle/oracle.py\"\n60\t        timeout_sec: 180\n61\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9fc9f22f-1ad2-4f8c-8c0a-cb7f3b7bd390","uuid":"950ff0dd-6a84-41a5-b31b-3a7acd4ed236","timestamp":"2026-06-23T21:17:00.838Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/mydata/karma/cases/ray/deploy_cluster/test.yaml","content":"# ray/deploy_cluster\n# Deploy a Ray head, head Service, and worker deployment from provided manifests\n\nprompt: |\n  A ray-client pod is running in the ray namespace, but no Ray cluster exists yet.\n\n  Your task: deploy a Ray head, a Ray head Service, and a Ray worker deployment\n  using the manifests in:\n  - cases/ray/deploy_cluster/resource/ray-head.yaml\n  - cases/ray/deploy_cluster/resource/ray-head-service.yaml\n  - cases/ray/deploy_cluster/resource/ray-worker.yaml\n\n  Requirements:\n  - Keep ray-client unchanged.\n  - The worker deployment should run {{params.worker_replicas}} replicas.\n\n  Use this command to validate:\n  ```bash\n  kubectl -n ray exec ray-client -- python -c \"import ray; ray.init(address='ray-head:6379'); print('ok'); ray.shutdown()\"\n  ```\n\n  Success criteria: both deployments are ready and the command prints \"ok\".\n\nparams:\n  worker_replicas:\n    default: 2\n    description: Number of replicas for the Ray worker deployment\n\nnamespace_contract:\n  required_roles: []\n\nmetrics:\n  - time_to_first_mutation\n\npreconditionUnits:\n  - name: ray_env_ready\n    on_probe_fail: skip\n    probe:\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\"\n        